12-18 20:59:33','','Fun Facts Icons-04','','inherit','open','closed','','fun-facts-icons-04','','','2015-12-18 20:59:33','2015-12-18 20:59:33','',3159,'https://inventiondevfund.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Fun-Facts-Icons-04.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3193,5,'2015-12-18 21:28:11','2015-12-18 21:28:11','<strong>December 17, 2015</strong> – Seoul, Korea – <a href=\"http://www.usa.lutronic.com/\">Lutronic Corporation</a>, a Korea-based company engaged in the manufacture of medical laser equipment, announced a strategic alliance with the Invention Development Fund (IDF) at Intellectual Ventures, a leading invention capital company, to expand its existing business, including its ophthalmology division.\r\n\r\nLutronic expects that its work with IDF will both strengthen its existing patent portfolio and create synergies in the development of new and innovative treatment technologies.\r\n\r\nThrough this strategic alliance, IDF will create complementary inventions or provide its own relevant patents that are helpful to Lutronic\'s ophthalmology business. IDF will also make its IP For Defense (IPFD) services available to Lutronic as it enters new areas of business.\r\n\r\nHaelyung HWANG, CEO of Lutronic commented that “Lutronic is a technology based company and currently has more than 200 Korean and international patents. Through this strategic alliance with IV, we will innovate to expand our ophthalmology business in the future.\"\r\n\r\nEdward Jung, CTO and one of the founders of IV said, “We are always on the lookout for strategically important, industry-leading companies such as Lutronic. I am confident that this project will result in groundbreaking inventions and innovations for Lutronic’s ophthalmology business. Ultimately, this alliance helps Lutronic innovate into new areas of growth.”\r\n\r\n<strong>About Intellectual Ventures and Invention Development Fund</strong>\r\n\r\nFounded in 2000, Intellectual Ventures (IV) is a privately-held invention capital company. With more than US$6 billion committed capital and more than 40,000 IP assets in active monetization programs, IV owns one of the world’s largest and fastest-growing intellectual property portfolios, which it licenses to the world’s most innovative companies. Investors include a mix of Fortune 500 companies, individuals, and institutions.\r\n\r\nThe Invention Development Fund (IDF) was established in 2007 as a new part of the Intellectual Ventures family of Investment Funds focused on building a global inventor network. IDF invents on behalf of its many customers in a variety of industries, ranging from huge multinational food and beverage or credit card companies to startups and regional SMEs. With employees in localized offices around the globe, IDF builds relationships with its closely-curated global network of more than 10,000 invention network members and more than 400 research institutions, universities, and companies. For more information about IDF, visit <a href=\"http://www.inventiondevfund.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.inventiondevfund.com</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Lutronic Corporation and Intellectual Ventures Enter Strategic Alliance','','publish','open','open','','lutronic-strategic-alliance','','','2015-12-18 21:28:11','2015-12-18 21:28:11','',0,'https://inventiondevfund.com/?p=3193',0,'post','',0),(3194,1,'2015-12-18 21:18:59','2015-12-18 21:18:59','','RFI150103--Transformational-Snacks-For-Home2','','inherit','open','closed','','rfi150103-transformational-snacks-for-home2','','','2015-12-18 21:18:59','2015-12-18 21:18:59','',3159,'https://inventiondevfund.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/RFI150103-Transformational-Snacks-For-Home2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3195,1,'2015-12-18 21:58:31','2015-12-18 21:58:31','','stock-photo-many-types-of-savoury-snack-in-white-dishes-200643878','','inherit','open','closed','','stock-photo-many-types-of-savoury-snack-in-white-dishes-200643878','','','2015-12-18 21:58:31','2015-12-18 21:58:31','',3159,'https://