ccess to an online portal for data analysis. Notably, the recently improved Boogio inserts now contain a thin battery, transmitter, and sensors all ergonomically integrated in a slim, standard-insole form factor.\r\n\r\nREFLX Labs has already been exploring motion-sensing applications for mobile games, virtual reality, fitness, and training – including physical rehabilitation uses in clinical settings. Building on their slogan “Make Any Shoe a Smart Shoe,” the availability of Boogio developer kits will now enable third-party developers to innovate in other potential application areas.\r\n\r\nREFLX Labs works in a strategic partnership with Intellectual Ventures’ Invention Development Fund (IDF) seeking to pave the way for innovation and the commercialization of Boogio wearable technology worldwide.\r\n\r\nTo learn more about REFLX Labs or to request a developer kit, please visit <a href=\"http://www.boogio.com\">www.boogio.com</a>.','Boogio Developer Kits Now Available','','publish','open','open','','boogiodevkits','','','2016-05-25 11:18:04','2016-05-25 18:18:04','',0,'https://inventiondevfund.com/?p=3339',0,'post','',0),(3342,5,'2016-02-10 23:46:41','2016-02-10 23:46:41','','Boogio Home','','inherit','open','closed','','boogio-home','','','2016-02-10 23:46:41','2016-02-10 23:46:41','',0,'https://inventiondevfund.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Boogio-Home.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3343,1,'2016-02-11 01:41:44','2016-02-11 01:41:44','','Transformational Snacks - Hero Video','','inherit','open','closed','','transformational-snacks-hero-video','','','2016-02-11 01:41:44','2016-02-11 01:41:44','',0,'https://inventiondevfund.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Transformational-Snacks-Hero-Video.mp4',0,'attachment','video/mp4',0),(3344,1,'2016-02-11 01:41:47','2016-02-11 01:41:47','','Transformational_Snacks_-_Hero_Video','','inherit','open','closed','','transformational_snacks_-_hero_video','','','2016-02-11 01:41:47','2016-02-11 01:41:47','',0,'https://inventiondevfund.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Transformational_Snacks_-_Hero_Video.ogv',0,'attachment','video/ogg',0),(3345,1,'2016-02-11 01:45:09','2016-02-11 01:45:09','','Transformational_Snacks_-_Hero_Video','','inherit','open','closed','','transformational_snacks_-_hero_video-2','','','2016-02-11 01:45:09','2016-02-11 01:45:09','',0,'https://inventiondevfund.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Transformational_Snacks_-_Hero_Video-1.ogv',0,'attachment','video/ogg',0),(3346,1,'2016-02-12 01:54:30','2016-02-12 01:54:30','[vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row_content_no_spaces\" padding_bottom=\"-80\" margin_bottom=\"-80\"][vc_column offset=\"vc_hidden-lg vc_hidden-md vc_hidden-sm\"][vc_single_image image=\"3443\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row\" padding_top=\"90\" padding_bottom=\"40\" font_color=\"#4d4d4d\" css=\".vc_custom_1441042963431{background-color: #f6f6f6 !important;}\"][vc_column width=\"1/6\"][vc_column_text]\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"2/3\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h1 style=\"font-size: 62px; text-align: center; font-family: lobster;\"><span style=\"color: #ff940e;\"><strong>Non-Thermal Pasteurization </strong></span></h1>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1457140458577{margin-top: -30px !important;}\"]\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">New cold pressed technologies are needed to increase throughput and shelf life while decreasing costs.</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/6\"][vc_column_text]\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row\" bg_type=\"image\" bg_image_pos=\"cover\" bg_image_att=\"fixed\" padding_top=\"40\" padding_bottom=\"40\" font_color=\"#212121\" bg_image=\"3349\"][vc_column][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1457140536528{margin-bottom: 0px !important;border-bottom-width: 0px !important;}\"]\r\n<h1 class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #ff940e; font-family: lobster; font-size: 50px;\">Market <strong>Trends</strong></span></h1>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner css=\".vc_custom_1441049736683{margin-top: -30px !important;}\"][vc_column_inner width=\"5/12\"][vc_column_text]\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"2/12\"][vc_separator color=\"custom\" border_width=\"3\" el_width=\"60\" accent_color=\"#7bc142\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"5/12\"][vc_column_text]\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"2/3\"][vc_raw_html]\r\n\r\nJTNDZGl2JTIwaWQlM0QlMjJjaGFydF9kaXYlMjIlM0UlM0MlMkZkaXYlM0UlMEE=\r\n\r\n[/vc_raw_html][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1456866008087{margin-top: 0px !important;border-top-width: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;}\"]\r\n<h4>Developing markets, such as Asia Pacific and Latin America, show an increased demand for juice products. In developed regions, the traditional juice market growth has slowed, but demand for cold-pressed or luxury juices is taking off.</h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1456866398703{margin-top: 0px !important;border-top-width: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;}\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3>The juice market has <span style=\"color: #ff940e;\"><strong>doubled in volume</strong></span> over the past decade</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3>Health trends have created a <span style=\"color: #ff940e;\"><strong>new demand for luxury juices</strong></span> in markets where these products previously did not exist</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3>Developing markets demand for <span style=\"color: #ff940e;\"><strong>packaged juice is on the rise</strong></span></h3>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3>Developed markets are seeing increased <span style=\"color: #ff940e;\"><strong>demand for cold-pressed juices</strong></span></h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"]\r\n[/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][om_moving_box content_type=\"icon\" icon_type=\"typicons\" color=\"custom\" custom_color=\"#e83a43\" icon_size=\"54px\" icon_typicons=\"typcn typcn-arrow-down\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"]\r\n[/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row\" bg_type=\"image\" padding_top=\"50\" font_color=\"#ffffff\" bg_image=\"3377\"][vc_column width=\"2/3\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left; font-family: lobster;\">Learn More by Joining Our Inventor Network</h1>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/3\" css=\".vc_custom_1456012756879{margin-top: 20px !important;}\"][vc_btn title=\"GET STARTED!\" color=\"custom\" size=\"xlg\" align=\"center\" link=\"url:https%3A%2F%2Fivin.intven.com%2Fsignup|title:IVIN%20Sign%20Up|target:%20_blank\" custom_color=\"#e83a43\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row_content\" bg_type=\"image\" font_color=\"#e83a43\" padding_top=\"40\" padding_bottom=\"10\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1457045965227{padding-left: 25px !important;}\"]\r\n<h1 style=\"font-size: 62px; font-family: lobster; text-transform: capitalize;\"><span style=\"color: #ff940e;\">Successful Non-Thermal Pasteurization Technologies </span><span style=\"color: #ff940e;\">Will:</span></h1>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"3380\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1456012395606{padding-left: 25px !important;}\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3><strong>Extend Shelf Life</strong> – 63 to 77 days minimum</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3><strong>Have Low Regulation</strong> – New tech should be GRAS (Generally Recognized As Safe)</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3><strong>Generate Consumer Acceptance</strong> – Must maintain a clean label and consumers must perceive it to be healthy</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3><strong>Cost Less</strong> – Equipment and operating costs must be lower than current technology</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1457044305122{padding-left: 25px !important;}\"]\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3><strong>Reduce Micro-organisms</strong> – Must achieve &gt;5-log reduction in pathogenic and spoilage micro-organism load</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3><strong>Have a High Processing Rate</strong> – Prefer at least 25 kilo-liters/hour</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3><strong>Consider Packaging</strong> – Advantageous if the product can be sterilized in its packaging</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3><strong>Maintain Low Heat</strong> – Temperature of the food cannot exceed 24<sup>o </sup>C</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"]\r\n[/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][om_moving_box content_type=\"icon\" icon_type=\"typicons\" color=\"custom\" custom_color=\"#7bc142\" icon_size=\"54px\" icon_typicons=\"typcn typcn-arrow-down\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"]\r\n[/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row_content\" bg_type=\"image\" bg_image_pos=\"cover\" font_color=\"#ffffff\" bg_image=\"3378\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\" css=\".vc_custom_1456012491129{margin-top: 20px !important;}\"][vc_single_image image=\"3381\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left; font-size: 50px; font-family: lobster;\">Current Technology is Lacking</h1>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_toggle title=\"Dense Phase Carbon Dioxide (DPCD) \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455310068421-07c427ac-7074\"]\r\n<h4>The rapid decompression of carbon dioxide from a pressure of 500lbs/in<sup>2</sup> to ambient pressure. This is milder and lower pressure than HPP. Current limitations are low solubility in strong polar substances and poor selectively of some solutes.</h4>\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Bacteriocins and Antimicrobial Ingredients \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455310060557-25073fdb-f11c\"]\r\n<h4>Biologically active peptides that inhibit the growth of spoilage or pathogenic bacteria. Current limitations with the range of bacteria they can inhibit.</h4>\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"High Pressure Processing (HPP) \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455310079465-7c8cc558-987d\"]\r\n<h4>Uses hydrostatic pressures to inactivate micro-organisms with minimal heating. Current limitations are high capital costs and low throughput.</h4>\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Pulsed Light (PL) and UV light \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455310031416-54e74c30-6b2d\"]\r\n<h4>Pulsed white light inactivates vegetative cells and spores on the surfaces of foods. Current limitations are in fluid foods where the micro-organisms are located far from the UV source and don’t receive photon contact because the fluid layer absorbs it.</h4>\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Pulsed Electric Field (PEF)\" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455310042702-f1fceb8a-eb11\"]\r\n<h4>High Voltage pulses reduce micro-organisms. PEF is limited to the types and viscosity of foods.  Liquid foods with small particles and the presence of bubbles diminish efficacy.</h4>\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Ozone/Cold Plasma \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455310050840-9bb9e08b-7a2d\"]\r\n<h4>Ozone (O3) applied to food is highly reactive and causes deactivation of micro-organisms. Current limitations are significant loss of color pigment, and high oxidization potential that degrades organic compounds.</h4>\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Enzymes\" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455309940384-181c3325-aa8c\"]\r\n<h4>Enzymes are purified from microbial cells then added to foods. Current limitations are the cost of the enzymes, and in some products they must be inactivated or removed after processing.</h4>\r\n[/vc_toggle][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row_content\" bg_type=\"image\" bg_image_pos=\"cover\" bg_image_att=\"parallax_down\" font_color=\"#ffffff\" padding_top=\"40\" bg_image=\"3437\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner css=\".vc_custom_1455312071756{margin-bottom: -30px !important;background-color: rgba(0,0,0,0.01) !important;background-position: center !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: cover !important;*background-color: rgb(0,0,0) !important;}\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"]\r\n[/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h1 style=\"font-size: 62px; font-family: lobster; text-transform: capitalize; text-align: center;\">Invention Suggestions</h1>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"]\r\n[/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_toggle title=\"Dense Phase Carbon Dioxide (DPCD) \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455311780296-6c2afb3c-6257\"]\r\n<h4>Solutions that focus on high-throughput. Commercial sized DPCD equipment with continuous operations is desired.</h4>\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Bacteriocins and Antimicrobial Ingredients \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455311740219-874949ed-1ca5\"]\r\n<h4>New bacteriocins and antimicrobial ingredients that are considered GRAS and can reduce micro-organism load and be accepted by consumers.</h4>\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"High Pressure Processing (HPP) \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455310573770-5f5fa983-25be\"]\r\n<h4>Invention solutions that allow for continuous, high volume HPP rather than batch or semi-continuous as well as those that combining HPP with other technologies (DPCD, Ultrasound, PEF or PL or UV).</h4>\r\n[/vc_toggle][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_toggle title=\"Pulsed Light (PL) and UV light \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455310572765-06a6612d-d9f8\"]\r\n<h4>Technologies that thin or aerosolize the liquid to the extent that light can penetrate all the liquid or solutions that incorporate light during pre or post processing to augment pasteurization.</h4>\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Pulsed Electric Field (PEF) \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455310574833-1be21196-f7c0\"]\r\n<h4>Solutions that resolve current limitations and include applications for liquid foods and those with small particles. Inventions for continuous, large capacity PEF equipment are desired.</h4>\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Ozone/Cold Plasma \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455311822594-6f9431e6-cab8\"]\r\n<h4>Because this technology has a tendency to destroy juices, it can’t be used during the processing stage. However during pre-processing, it has little effect on whole fruits and vegetables while reducing micro-organisms. Solutions that improve or integrate this with other technologies would be considered.</h4>\r\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Enzymes\" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455311705783-152f440d-863c\"]\r\n<h4>New enzymes that are considered GRAS and can reduce micro-organism load and be accepted by consumers.</h4>\r\n[/vc_toggle][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row_content_no_spaces\" css=\".vc_custom_1441042786961{margin-bottom: -40px !important;padding-top: 80px !important;padding-bottom: 70px !important;background-color: #8ec549 !important;}\" padding_top=\"-10\" font_color=\"#ffffff\" padding_bottom=\"-10\" bg_color=\"#194265\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\" delimiter=\"vline\" css=\".vc_custom_1449953324432{padding-top: 40px !important;padding-bottom: 40px !important;}\"][om_box text_color=\"#ffffff\"]\r\n<h2 style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">JOIN THE IVIN COMMUNITY TO VIEW MORE OPPORTUNITIES</h2>\r\n[ividf_signup][/om