//www.researchgate.net/profile/David_Huer]\r\n\r\nNevertheless, going forward, it is not something I want to repeat. Too costly.\r\n\r\nIs early partnering with a disruptive inventor/entrepreneur something that IV would contemplate?\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\n\r\n\r\nDavid Huer\r\n\r\nAbout me\r\n\r\nUnorthodox thinker/entrepreneur/operations efficiency consultant,\r\nknown for solving intractable problems by noticing the tiniest of clues.\r\n\r\nPrevious venture - WarriorHealth CombatCare\r\nDetails at https://angel.co/david-huer-01 \r\n\r\nExamples outside venturing:\r\nhttp://davehuer.com/solving-wicked-problems/\r\n* http://davehuer.com/bcitfolio/innoprojects/inno-shaker.html (creating an \"impossible-to-make\" machined part)\r\n* http://davehuer.com/bcitfolio/innoprojects/inno-minden.html (teaching an \"impossible-to-teach\" disabled student to roll a whitewater kayak)\r\n* http://davehuer.com/bcitfolio/innoprojects/inno-spraydeck.html (solving a 6-year-old, \"impossible-to-solve\" design flaw'),(56,12,1,7,'Andrew Celentano'),(57,12,1,2,'(781) 314-0707'),(58,12,1,3,'acelentano@boston-engineering.com'),(59,12,1,4,'CIO Conference NY'),(60,12,1,6,'Boston Engineering is comprised of about 70+ engineers, has been around for 20 years and is known for its work in the robotics world and motor-control in general.  I spoke with Jeri and am interested in exploring how we might participate.'),(61,13,1,7,'Allan J Barberio'),(62,13,1,2,'(941) 356-6522'),(63,13,1,3,'abarberio1@gmail.com'),(64,13,1,4,'You found me .'),(65,13,1,6,'I am part of a group that hold three provisional patents on a video needle syringe and related micro video imager. I think the next best step would be to partner with a major medical device manufacturer. Can you be of any help please?\r\nThanks\r\nAllan'),(66,14,1,7,'Sam Martin'),(67,14,1,2,'(028) 003-5762'),(68,14,1,3,'sam.martin@siworldforum.com'),(69,14,1,4,'Word of Mouth'),(70,14,1,6,'Hi,  \r\n\r\nI know you\'re busy so I\'ll try to keep it quick!  \r\n\r\nFirstly, let me introduce myself. I’m Sam Martin the Founder of the Strategy &amp; Innovation World Forum.   \r\n\r\nI wanted to reach out and introduce you to the forum as it arrives in Sydney for the first time on the 26th &amp; 27th of May, 2016.   \r\n\r\nFacebook, Woolworths, Groupon, ANZ, Dominos, GE, Metcash, AMP, Bupa, Sanofi &amp; IAG are among those attending the event.   \r\n\r\nhttp://www.worldforumdisrupt.com/strategy-innovation-sydney-2016/  \r\n\r\nThe forum provides a platform for innovative consultancies to promote their services to our audience of decision makers in a number of different ways. \r\n   \r\nIt would be good to discuss how we can get you in front of our executive audience. \r\n\r\nThanks, \r\nSam'),(71,15,1,7,'Stephen van Rooyen'),(72,15,1,2,'(081) 578-0850'),(73,15,1,3,'sotheby3000@gmail.com'),(74,15,1,4,'refferal'),(75,15,1,6,'Good Day\r\n\r\nI would like to submit my invention for consideration under the partnership programme.\r\n\r\nPlease get back to me.\r\n\r\nStephen van Rooyen'),(76,16,1,7,'Steven Sable'),(77,16,1,2,'(800) 790-0437'),(78,16,1,3,'steven@visionarythinkinggroup.com'),(79,16,1,4,'Web search'),(80,16,1,6,'I have a small firm who devotes all our time to developing new products to address known or unknown market needs.\r\n\r\nWe have a portfolio of pre-patented products which we would like to have you consider for inclusion into your portfolio.\r\n\r\nWe have done IP searches and have declared all our approaches in the clear.  \r\n\r\nWe had two separate subject matter experts evaluate a potential global market value for the entire portfolio.  The life-of-product consensus exceeds US$4B.'),(81,17,1,7,'William (Bill) Drewes'),(82,17,1,2,'(281) 668-8340'),(83,17,1,3,'Billd@Verbatim-VR.com'),(84,17,1,4,'Above phone is USA - Messages Only'),(85,17,1,6,'Dr. Patrick Ennis\r\nGlobal Head of Technology\r\n\r\nDear Dr. Ennis\r\n\r\nI would like to send you an email regarding our new high impact technology, which is actively 