ts of delivering CEVTTEN to One Subcounty is  $US 9,500 (United States Dollars Nine Thousand Five Hundred only).\r\nPolicy Guidelines: Beneficiaries who are Six(6) in numbers –women and men in equal proportion selected and nominated by their localities for the CEVTTEN training from each of 15 villages that comprise 25 Parishes forming  Ibuje subcounty, in Maruzi county, Apac District, northern Uganda.\r\n·        Upon successfully completing CEVTTEN training in Ibuje Subcounty, the programme will be conducted into the other Subcounties which comprise Maruzi County in Apac District, namely:\r\n-        Akokoro Subcounty                         ( training cost: $US 9,500)\r\n-        Apac Subcounty                                ( Training costs: $US 9,500)\r\n-        Chegere Subcounty                        (training costs: $US 9,500)\r\n-        -Chawente Subcounty                  ( training cost: $US 9,500)\r\n-        Then winding/wrapping up the CEVTTEN phase one programme in Maruzi County- whereby each Subcounty package shall have cost $US 9,500, times (United States Dollars Forty Seven thousand Five Hundred only).\r\n\r\n-        The above cost ( $US 47,500) is the Financial Requirement Package   to enable effective delivering CEVTTEN programme in Apac District alone.\r\n\r\n-        there are 137 Districts in Uganda as in 2013, this will mean multiply the CEVTTEN programme cost per District with 137\r\n-      Thus= $US 47,500 per district x 137 districts throughout Uganda  = $US 6,497,500(United States Dollars  Six Million,Four ninety Seven thousand Five Hundred only)\r\n\r\nOutputs of CEVTTEN PROGRAMMES:-\r\n\r\n-       Training Outputs then would be multiply 750 trainees per District  TIMES  (x)  137 Districts equals =  102,750(One Hundred and Two Thousand, Seven fifty) Ugandans shall have been trained throughout the country with direct connections and links and cooperation with the Five Topmost  District Government Offices and Directorates, namely Offices