INSERT INTO `qtx_rg_lead_detail_long` VALUES (25,'I\'ve been mulling over a number of ideas including (since the early 1980s) a ship design innovation that would reduce transportation costs, and significantly enhance the profitability of shipping companies. I am passionate about generating useful new ideas, and would be delighted to be a part of an ecosystem that lets me focus on my strengths, instead of on the parts of the innovation and patent value chain that have been bottlenecks (for me) in the past. Best, Imon'),(30,'I have an idea for a change to a very basic device that has remained unchanged for hundreds of years. I believe this improvement will benefit perhaps hundreds of thousands of people, making life easier for them. I have tinkered with making it happen, but haven\'t quite figured it out yet. I know that this will work, but am not mechanically inclined. Would be interested with sharing my idea for some revenue sharing. This is a simple, life altering improvement.'),(35,'I am a Mexican Inventor, with several Patents in Mexico, and a lot of Patent initiatives to apply, looking for the right Partner for two key aspects:\r\n1.- Start a US Company to have access to Fed Grants as an American Company.\r\n2. Move the inventions to the experimental lab and then to the market, to create wealth,\r\nAs a serial Inventor, I have initiatives in several fields like Power energy transmission, earthquake column design, beam design, precision liquid dispensers, heavy truck axes design, osmosis filters, irrigation systems for the native tree transplantation in order to prevent a non-reverse erosion, improving plankton CO2 capture, exercise equipment for obese and people in physical  rehabilitation, educational games, innovation process learning by repetitive practice in my Knowledge Labyrinth, and so on and on.'),(40,'Hello I have some important innovations in the field of sanitary ware and fans and others - it is very necessary and very simple (I mean, God willing, the project successful 100%) - that provide (((((enough money and an international marketing))))) The profits will be A millions of dollars to their products - iam looking for a factory or financiers. - if you have this possibility or you can provide A large factory or funded PLEASE CALL ME the Innovation its not complicated and 100 % will be success and you will see that after we make and sink to the markets a lot of factories will make it ------------------------ Clarify \\ Summary of all that we wrote: - - We will make ordinary tap and provided to each house to buy one at minimum ))) (and I expect will make more than 300 million of that product inevitably sooner or later --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- And when we have made our products hit the market, and millions of her sisters neglect Because it is the success of our product is very important and necessary for each house'),(50,'Intellectual Ventures has developed a technology that could play an essential part of a concept/invention I am interested in testing the viability of.  I would like to know if IV is interested in considering this.\r\nThe phone entry format on your webpage isn\'t accepting the number I tried to enter which is + (NZ code from USA) 64 27 4192085 but email is preferable.\r\nRegards\r\nVaughan Maybury'),(55,'Hello from Vancouver, Canada,\r\n\r\nI\'ve noticed a way to break IP owned by Intel through its acquisition of another company. Reached out to the acquired company, to Intel, and other companies but no response. \r\nPerhaps they are wracking their brains trying to figure out the gap? \r\n\r\nI\'d like to take this forward as part of a venture I am building out, a disruptive tech incubator, where we license or exit patentable tech solutions. Noticing tiny clues is what I do, but asking now before creating filings because of experience with my venture WarriorHealth CombatCare. It is simply too costly and time-consuming to breach the encirclement of a massive entity. Although, it can be fun--helping my veteran customers win by helping a giant competitor lose was incredibly satisfying [UBC/VCHRI demanded the right to show IP to patent aggregators during NDA negotiations without assured compensation or benefit, or even an explanation to take to investors; and this was unacceptable, as I wanted assured swiftness of experiments to benefit my veteran customers. And open-sourced everything instead: http://www.researchgate.net/profile/David_Huer]\r\n\r\nNevertheless, going forward, it is not something I want to repeat. Too costly.\r\n\r\nIs early partnering with a disruptive inventor/entrepreneur something that IV would contemplate?\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\n\r\n\r\nDavid Huer\r\n\r\nAbout me\r\n\r\nUnorthodox thinker/entrepreneur/operations efficiency consultant,\r\nknown for solving intractable problems by noticing the tiniest of clues.\r\n\r\nPrevious venture - WarriorHealth CombatCare\r\nDetails at https://angel.co/david-huer-01 \r\n\r\nExamples outside venturing:\r\nhttp://davehuer.com/solving-wicked-problems/\r\n* http://davehuer.com/bcitfolio/innoprojects/inno-shaker.html (creating an \"impossible-to-make\" machined part)\r\n* http://davehuer.com/bcitfolio/innoprojects/inno-minden.html (teaching an \"impossible-to-teach\" disabled student to roll a whitewater kayak)\r\n* http://davehuer.com/bcitfolio/innoprojects/inno-spraydeck.html (solving a 6-year-old, \"impossible-to-solve\" design flaw'),(60,'Boston Engineering is comprised of about 70+ engineers, has been around for 20 years and is known for its work in the robotics world and motor-control in general.  I spoke with Jeri and am interested in exploring how we might participate.'),(65,'I am part of a group that hold three provisional patents on a video needle syringe and related micro video imager. I think the next best step would be to partner with a major medical device manufacturer. Can you be of any help please?\r\nThanks\r\nAllan'),(70,'Hi,  \r\n\r\nI know you\'re busy so I\'ll try to keep it quick!  \r\n\r\nFirstly, let me introduce myself. I’m Sam Martin the Founder of the Strategy &amp; Innovation World Forum.   \r\n\r\nI wanted to reach out and introduce you to the forum as it arrives in Sydney for the first time on the 26th &amp; 27th of May, 2016.   \r\n\r\nFacebook, Woolworths, Groupon, ANZ, Dominos, GE, Metcash, AMP, Bupa, Sanofi &amp; IAG are among those attending the event.   \r\n\r\nhttp://www.worldforumdisrupt.com/strategy-innovation-sydney-2016/  \r\n\r\nThe forum provides a platform for innovative consultancies to promote their services to our audience of decision makers in a number of different ways. \r\n   \r\nIt would be good to discuss how we can get you in front of our executive audience. \r\n\r\nThanks, \r\nSam'),(80,'I have a small firm who devotes all our time to developing new products to address known or unknown market needs.\r\n\r\nWe have a portfolio of pre-patented products which we would like to have you consider for inclusion into your portfolio.\r\n\r\nWe have done IP searches and have declared all our approaches in the clear.  \r\n\r\nWe had two separate subject matter experts evaluate a potential global market value for the entire portfolio.  The life-of-product consensus exceeds US$4B.'),(85,'Dr. Patrick Ennis\r\nGlobal Head of Technology\r\n\r\nDear Dr. Ennis\r\n\r\nI would like to send you an email regarding our new high impact technology, which is actively endorsed by Dr. Rita Singh, Senior Research Systems Scientist, Language Technology Institute at Carnegie Mellon University who is our “Senior Sage, Mentor &amp; Advisor” .\r\n\r\nWould you please be so kind as to send your email address to me. \r\n\r\nYours truly, \r\n\r\n William (Bill) Drewes \r\nFounder &amp; CEO\r\nVERBATIM-VR\r\n57 Ahronson Street\r\nHadera, Israel \r\nWebsite: www.Verbatim-VR.com \r\nE-Mail: Billd@Verbatim-VR.com'),(90,'Let first introduce me to you, I am in life after retirement and I\r\n have an idea which needed to be developed.\r\n\r\n This technology is a leverage spinning rod technology. Let me brief\r\n about the principal and features of this tech.\r\n The baseline of tech is 100 % free from pollution 100 % manual for\r\n three-wheelers, four-wheelers and wheelchairs are my focal point of\r\n invention at the moment.\r\n Easy driving in terms of speed it is second to none.  To reach this speed\r\n by other vehicles need to burn much pollutant fuel which is polluting\r\n the air what people breath.\r\n\r\n When I saw a picture many years ago of a handicapped person on the\r\n bicycle rickshaw riding it with hand pedal fitted it in to hand\r\n position on his lap a cute baby girl may be 4 to 5 years of age on his lap\r\n in sound sleep. This man rotating hand pedal for the distance about 20\r\n km far away to the school of his lovely daughter two times a day. His\r\n pain and endurance what I found was immeasurable.  That is the time I\r\n began to think  if there is some easy version of technology it  can\r\n make easier and faster to reach the destination  then it will  be a\r\n great relief for these poor people on the wheelchairs.  From that\r\n moment my mind and brain set journey in search of an easy method. I\r\n did many home work and calculations. It was continuous mental\r\n processes and collisions with various ideas fleeting trough mind.\r\n Very recently happened  to see a man on the wheelchair struggle so\r\n much to roll the wheel across a busy road.  How it was so risky and\r\n how many times and how fast he has to turn the wheel to reach the\r\n other side of the road. If they get a easy method of riding system it\r\n will be great relief for them and also a new lease of life with new\r\n technology by thus  I feel I fulfill  my dream some\r\n by contributing some thing good for them. By this time I arrived at an\r\n idea, 25 years after I  saw the picture on the news paper about the\r\n handicapped person on the bicycle rickshaw pedal connected to his hand\r\n position. This man\r\n was physically handicapped myself financially handicapped in the sense\r\n we both of us are on the same boat that is the reason even I arrived\r\n at the idea in the year 2013 from  that time onward I also struggle to make a\r\n prototype of one of these items. Patent Prior Art Search Report Ref. No\r\n 6209/CHE/2015/bs/ 108.\r\n\r\n Their report follows\r\n\r\n The Patent Report as follows\r\n  New -Based on the prior art utility model increases a leverage and\r\n crankshaft connecting rod system to achieve better labor-saving effect\r\n for two- wheel, three-wheeler or four-wheel rickshaws.\r\n\r\n  Old- Whereas the common rickshaw even harder particularly in condition\r\n of large velocity ratio, there by having relatively slow speed. Rider\r\n feel hard when using driving device of common rickshaw\r\n\r\n New-The utility model compared with the prior art, due to increased\r\n leverage and toggle link mechanism, so that food circular motion\r\n around the rotation is converted to the reciprocating motion of number\r\n of levers, so achieve the purpose of the effort.\r\n\r\n Cursory review-  The pedal end region of crank is connected to the\r\n circular ring by a pin and bearing arrangement. Preferably,  to\r\n facilitate the guided circular motion of the pedal along the circular\r\n ring, the circular ring is provided as guide for the rotary motion of\r\n the pedal. In accordance with embodiment of pedal-crank system of the\r\n invention such  slidable increase of the length of pedal arm\r\n selectively during it rotary motion is possible by way of providing\r\n the pedal arm to slide with in a guide while pedal - crank system\r\n rotates. For  the purpose of the pivot of pedal-crank assembly is\r\n placed behind the center of circular ring and very close to said\r\n circular ring with pin on each pedal arm opposite to the pedal foot\r\n rest inserted through ball bearing into a groove in said circular\r\n ring. The other end of pedal arm is maintained free and the whole arm\r\n is adopted to slide in with in aguide/slotted bracket. This system\r\n almost double the torque of conventional pedal-crank generated by way\r\n of pedal-crank of the invention.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n Summary of Result\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n During the prior art search found the invention noteworthy, efficient\r\n application and cost effective and this leverage technology favor to\r\n all mechanical driven subjects\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n No highly relevant prior art encompassing all the features of the\r\n given invention such as was found.\r\n\r\n The search was focused on cycle rickshaw with the leverage system\r\n which aids the wheel to roll faster and easier, where in\r\n\r\n Leverage system with spinner moving through spinner rod\r\n\r\n Reduce pollution\r\n\r\n Increase speed\r\n\r\n Achieve longer distance in shorter timing\r\n\r\n Reduce pulling pressure.\r\n\r\n The following prior considered as noteworthy  reference and given under List B\r\n\r\n During course of search, one web reference relating to a cycle\r\n rickshaw was found and it is considered as interesting web reference\r\n and given under the title Non Patent Literature.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n A simple and cost effective manner of improving the torque generated\r\n through pedal-crank system which would favor drivers and efficient\r\n application of such as pedal-crank system  in variety of mechanical\r\n driven subjects.\r\n\r\n  I am quite content with this patent report and thanks to everyone\r\n worked for this Patent Report which favors  the need of the hour.\r\n Wheelchair can be driven with fingers control by pressing upward by\r\n connected bar in finger position. By single slow presser up word by\r\n fingers wheelchair start to roll about 350 feet distance it can be\r\n slower or faster. By suitable modification with sunshield it can be\r\n used for long distance travels.\r\n\r\n I wish to have your kind perusal although I am not sure who ge